To create an engaging line chart that illustrates the trend of movie productions over the years using Vega-Lite, we need to focus on the attributes that can give us insights into the number of movies produced each year. Unfortunately, the provided data point lacks an explicit 'Year' attribute; however, it includes a 'Release Date'. We can extract the year from the 'Release Date' to determine the production trend over time. Here's the Vega-Lite JSON specification for the line chart:

```json
{
  "$schema": "https://vega.github.io/schema/vega-lite/v5.json",
  "description": "A line chart showing the trend of movie productions over the years based on release dates.",
  "data": {
    "url": "data/movies.json",
    "format": {
      "type": "json",
      "property": "data"
    }
  },
  "transform": [
    {
      "calculate": "year(datum['Release Date'])",
      "as": "Release Year"
    }
  ],
  "mark": "line",
  "encoding": {
    "x": {
      "field": "Release Year",
      "type": "temporal",
      "timeUnit": "year",
      "axis": {
        "title": "Year"
      }
    },
    "y": {
      "aggregate": "count",
      "field": "Title",
      "type": "quantitative",
      "axis": {
        "title": "Number of Movies"
      }
    },
    "tooltip": [
      {"field": "Release Year", "type": "temporal", "title": "Year"},
      {"aggregate": "count", "field": "Title", "type": "quantitative", "title": "Number of Movies"}
    ]
  },
  "width": 600,
  "height": 400
}
```

This specification uses the Vega-Lite library to parse the JSON data, calculate the release year from the release date, and display the trend of movie productions over time. The x-axis represents the year, and the y-axis represents the count of movies released each year. The tooltip provides additional interactivity, showing the exact year and the number of movies produced when hovering over the line.

