To delve deeper into the financial aspects of movies, particularly exploring the correlation between movie budget and return on investment (ROI), we need to create a scatter plot. This plot will allow us to analyze how different budgets impact the financial success of movies, potentially highlighting genre-specific and temporal trends. Here's how we can construct this in Vega-Lite JSON specification:

```json
{
  "$schema": "https://vega.github.io/schema/vega-lite/v5.json",
  "description": "A scatter plot showing the correlation between movie budget and return on investment.",
  "data": {
    "url": "data/movies.json",
    "format": {
      "type": "json",
      "property": "data"
    }
  },
  "transform": [
    {
      "calculate": "datum['Worldwide Gross'] / datum['Production Budget']",
      "as": "ROI"
    }
  ],
  "mark": "point",
  "encoding": {
    "x": {
      "field": "Production Budget",
      "type": "quantitative",
      "title": "Production Budget ($)",
      "axis": {
        "grid": false
      }
    },
    "y": {
      "field": "ROI",
      "type": "quantitative",
      "title": "Return on Investment",
      "axis": {
        "grid": false
      }
    },
    "color": {
      "field": "Major Genre",
      "type": "nominal",
      "legend": {
        "title": "Genre"
      }
    },
    "tooltip": [
      {"field": "Title", "type": "nominal", "title": "Movie Title"},
      {"field": "Production Budget", "type": "quantitative", "title": "Budget ($)"},
      {"field": "Worldwide Gross", "type": "quantitative", "title": "Worldwide Gross ($)"},
      {"field": "ROI", "type": "quantitative", "title": "ROI"},
      {"field": "Major Genre", "type": "nominal", "title": "Genre"}
    ]
  },
  "width": 600,
  "height": 400
}
```

This scatter plot uses the `Production Budget` as the x-axis and the calculated `ROI` as the y-axis. Each point on the plot represents a movie, with colors distinguishing different genres. The tooltip provides detailed information about each movie, including its title, budget, worldwide gross, and ROI, offering a comprehensive view of the financial performance relative to the budget.

